<inglise> COUNCIL REGULATION (EEC, EURATOM, ECSC) No 3765/92 of 21 December 1992 correcting, with effect from 1 January 1991, the weightings applicable in Denmark, Germany, Greece, Spain, France, Ireland, Italy, the Netherlands, Portugal and the United Kingdom to the remuneration and pensions of officials and other servants of the European Communities </inglise>
<eesti> N&Otilde;UKOGU M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (EM&Uuml;, Euratom, EST&Uuml;) nr 3765/92, millega parandatakse alates 1. jaanuarist 1991 Euroopa &uuml;henduste ametnike ja muude teenistujate t&ouml;&ouml;tasude ja pensionide suhtes Taanis, Saksamaal, Kreekas, Hispaanias, Prantsusmaal, Iirimaal, Itaalias, Madalmaades, Portugalis ja &Uuml;hendkuningriigis kohaldatavaid paranduskoefitsiente 21. detsember 1992 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing a Single Council and a Single Commission of the European Communities, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &uuml;henduste &uuml;htse n&otilde;ukogu ja &uuml;htse komisjoni asutamislepingut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Staff Regulations of Officials and the Conditions of Employment of Other Servants of the European Communities laid down by Regulation (EEC, Euratom, ECSC) No 259/68 (1), as last amended by Regulation (EEC, Euratom, ECSC) No 571/92 (2), and in particular Articles 64 and 82 of the Staff Regulations and the first paragraph of Article 20 and Article 64 of the Conditions of Employment, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &uuml;henduste ametnike personalieeskirju ja &uuml;henduste muude teenistujate teenistustingimusi, mis on s&auml;testatud m&auml;&auml;ruses (EM&Uuml;, Euratom, EST&Uuml;) nr 259/68, (1) viimati muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (EM&Uuml;, Euratom, EST&Uuml;) nr 571/92, (2) eriti personalieeskirjade artikleid 64 ja 82 ning teenistustingimuste artikli 20 esimest l&otilde;iku ja artiklit 64, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Decision 81/1061/Euratom, ECSC, EEC of 15 December 1981 amending the method of adjusting the remuneration of officials and other servants of the Communities (3), and in particular the second subparagraph of Section II.1.1 of the Annex thereto, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 15. detsembri 1981. aasta otsust 81/1061/Euratom, EST&Uuml;, EM&Uuml;, millega muudetakse &uuml;henduste ametnike ja muude teenistujate t&ouml;&ouml;tasu kohandamise meetodit, (3) eriti selle lisa II jao punkti 1.1 teist l&otilde;iku, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the proposal from the Commission, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse komisjoni ettepanekut </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the Statistical Office of the European Communities has carried out a verification of the weightings for all Member States in accordance with the method for adjusting the remuneration of officials and other servants of the European Communities, as adopted by the Council on 15 December 1981; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Statistikaamet on kontrollinud k&otilde;igi liikmesriikide puhul kasutatavaid paranduskoefitsiente vastavalt Euroopa &uuml;henduste ametnike ja muude teenistujate t&ouml;&ouml;tasu kohandamise meetodile, mille n&otilde;ukogu v&otilde;ttis vastu 15. detsembril 1981; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the findings of this verification have shown that the weightings that ought to be applied in a number of countries of employment diverge significantly from those in force; </inglise>
<eesti> nimetatud kontrollimise tulemused n&auml;itavad, et mitmes t&ouml;&ouml;kohariigis erinevad paranduskoefitsiendid, mida tuleks kohaldada, m&auml;rkimisv&auml;&auml;rselt tegelikult kohaldatavatest paranduskoefitsientidest; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Article 64 of the Staff Regulations provides for equivalence of purchasing power between the various places of employment; </inglise>
<eesti> personalieeskirjade artiklis 64 on s&auml;testatud, et ostuj&otilde;ud peaks eri t&ouml;&ouml;tamiskohtades olema v&otilde;rdv&auml;&auml;rne; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas it is necessary, if the preliminary weightings applicable in some places of employment are adjusted upwards, to adjust accordingly with retroactive effect remuneration of the officials concerned and, if weightings are adjusted downwards, to recover from the officials concerned the amounts paid in excess; </inglise>
<eesti> kui m&otilde;ningates t&ouml;&ouml;tamiskohtades kohaldatavaid esialgseid paranduskoefitsiente kohandatakse k&otilde;rgemaks, tuleb asjaomaste ametnike t&ouml;&ouml;tasusid vastavalt sellele kohandada tagasiulatuva j&otilde;uga, ning juhul kui koefitsiente kohandatakse madalamaks, tuleb liigselt makstud summad ametnikelt tagasi n&otilde;uda; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas it is necessary however to protect the nominal value of remuneration of the officials from whom amounts are to be recovered; </inglise>
<eesti> tuleks siiski kaitsta nende ametnike t&ouml;&ouml;tasu nimiv&auml;&auml;rtust, kellelt k&otilde;nealused summad tagasi n&otilde;utakse; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, in certain places of employment where the weightings are lower as compared with those in force when this Regulation will take effect for the first time, provision should be made for a phased application by set-off against any increases to be made at a future date; </inglise>
<eesti> teatavates t&ouml;&ouml;tamiskohtades, kus paranduskoefitsiendid on madalamad kui k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse esmakordse j&otilde;ustumise ajal kehtivad koefitsiendid, tuleks ette n&auml;ha j&auml;rkj&auml;rguline kohaldamine edaspidiste v&otilde;imalike suurendamiste tasaarvestamisega; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas it is therefore necesssary to amend the Regulations establishing, with effect form 1 January 1991, the weightings applicable to Denmark, Germany, Greece, Spain, France, Ireland, Italy, the Netherlands, the United Kingdom and Portugal, </inglise>
<eesti> seep&auml;rast tuleks muuta m&auml;&auml;rusi, millega on kehtestatud alates 1. jaanuarist 1991 Taanis, Saksamaal, Kreekas, Hispaanias, Prantsusmaal, Iirimaal, Itaalias, Madalmaades, &Uuml;hendkuningriigis ja Portugalis kohaldatavad paranduskoefitsiendid, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
